01:14:01,160 --> 01:14:03,440
- I don't need to go.
- I'm taking you.

992
01:14:03,440 --> 01:14:07,035
Oh, for God's sake,
I can get myself to the doctor.

993
01:14:15,200 --> 01:14:17,840
Look, I only came
because my husband insisted.

994
01:14:17,840 --> 01:14:21,320
I just wanted to set his mind at rest.
I know there's nothing wrong with me.

995
01:14:21,320 --> 01:14:23,960
I think you have post-traumatic stress disorder.

996
01:14:23,960 --> 01:14:26,360
I'm sorry but that is rubbish.

997
01:14:26,360 --> 01:14:29,520
Nothing happened to me,
it all happened to them.

998
01:14:29,520 --> 01:14:35,038
Absorbing other people's pain
is a stress of its own.

999
01:14:36,360 --> 01:14:38,680
I can't stop.

1000
01:14:38,680 --> 01:14:40,640
There's no-one else.

1001
01:14:40,640 --> 01:14:42,232
If I...

1002
01:16:30,720 --> 01:16:32,680
<i>And she hasn't stopped.</i>

1003
01:16:32,680 --> 01:16:34,960
<i>Oh, Margaret, Lovely to see you,</i>

1004
01:16:34,960 --> 01:16:36,840
Hello.

1005
01:16:36,840 --> 01:16:38,680
Margaret, hi.

1006
01:16:38,680 --> 01:16:40,716
Hope you don't mind us dropping in on you.

1007
01:16:42,200 --> 01:16:45,600
I was just telling them, Margaret,
we had such a good day.

1008
01:16:45,600 --> 01:16:48,520
I really wanted to invite you
but we know you're so busy.

1009
01:16:48,520 --> 01:16:51,040
30 years I was working at that pub.

1010
01:16:51,040 --> 01:16:52,720
And they never knew I had a daughter.

1011
01:16:52,720 --> 01:16:55,640
She was really keen for me
to come over for the retirement party

1012
01:16:55,640 --> 01:16:58,360
but we didn't know
what we were going to tell people.

1013
01:16:58,360 --> 01:17:00,680
- Then Bill says...
- Bill's one of the regulars.

1014
01:17:00,680 --> 01:17:02,560
'Who's this lovely young lady, Vera?'

1015
01:17:02,560 --> 01:17:05,120
He's ancient, see, so...

1016
01:17:05,120 --> 01:17:08,480
And I said, 'This is my daughter, Bill.

1017
01:17:08,480 --> 01:17:10,760
My daughter Charlotte.'

1018
01:17:10,760 --> 01:17:12,960
- And he says...
- Never even blinked.

1019
01:17:12,960 --> 01:17:14,840
..'She looks just like you.'

1020
01:17:14,840 --> 01:17:17,480
- He could tell.
- Anyone could tell.

1021
01:17:17,480 --> 01:17:21,000
And there we were in front of them all, together.

1022
01:17:21,000 --> 01:17:22,760
Mother and daughter.

1023
01:17:22,760 --> 01:17:25,880
- I tell you, Margaret...
- It was the happiest moment...

1024
01:17:25,880 --> 01:17:27,960
- Of my life.
- Both of us.

1025
01:17:27,960 --> 01:17:33,760
We just... We just felt... whole.

1026
01:17:33,760 --> 01:17:35,880
At last.

1027
01:17:35,880 --> 01:17:38,160
Nothing missing.

1028
01:17:38,160 --> 01:17:40,120
I said, 'We have to come and tell Margaret.'

1029
01:17:40,120 --> 01:17:43,360
But we didn't even know
if you'd be here, you're so busy.

1030
01:17:43,360 --> 01:17:46,557
So when are you back off to Australia?

1031
01:17:49,440 --> 01:17:51,954
Well, as soon as this lot can spare me.

1032
01:18:13,320 --> 01:18:16,120
There's a chilled chardonnay
on the table there for you.

1033
01:18:16,120 --> 01:18:20,320
Margaret River.
Bit young but hitting its stride, I reckon.

1034
01:18:20,320 --> 01:18:22,520
I didn't come here to drink, Len.

1035
01:18:22,520 --> 01:18:24,280
I thought you wanted to talk.

1036
01:18:24,280 --> 01:18:26,840
I do. I've got some soup too. It's home-cooked.

1037
01:18:26,840 --> 01:18:29,000
I can cook, you know.

1038
01:18:29,000 --> 01:18:30,520
I'm sure you can.

1039
01:18:30,520 --> 01:18:33,200
- You look hungry enough.
- I've already eaten.

1040
01:18:33,200 --> 01:18:36,120
What was it you wanted to say?

1041
01:18:36,120 --> 01:18:39,157
You're a difficult woman to entertain,
Mrs. Humphreys.

1042
01:18:42,560 --> 01:18:43,629
All right.

1043
01:19:02,160 --> 01:19:07,440
Look, um, all this TV coverage,
it's stirred everything up, Margaret.

1044
01:19:07,440 --> 01:19:09,960
It's got the boys talking.

1045
01:19:09,960 --> 01:19:14,320
And, um, I've been watching
how the boys are around you,

1046
01:19:14,320 --> 01:19:17,835
and, uh, not speaking out of turn,
you know what I'm talking about.

1047
01:19:19,040 --> 01:19:21,320
You're like a sister to them.

1048
01:19:21,320 --> 01:19:24,880
You're family after everything you've done.

1049
01:19:24,880 --> 01:19:28,240
You know? Only family
most of us will ever have anyway.

1050
01:19:28,240 --> 01:19:30,480
I'm not sure that family is really the right word.

1051
01:19:30,480 --> 01:19:32,440
Well, that's how we feel.

1052
01:19:32,440 --> 01:19:37,309
No, but you're right, it's... it's not real.

1053
01:19:39,400 --> 01:19:42,040
'Cause you haven't been there, have you?

1054
01:19:42,040 --> 01:19:46,040
You've heard about our childhood
but you haven't touched our childhood.

1055
01:19:46,040 --> 01:19:47,760
'Cause you haven't been there.

1056
01:19:47,760 --> 01:19:49,080
Where?

1057
01:19:49,080 --> 01:19:50,560
To Bindoon.

1058
01:19:50,560 --> 01:19:56,078
I'm, uh... I'm asking you
to come to Bindoon with me.

1059
01:19:58,640 --> 01:20:00,358
No.

1060
01:20:02,200 --> 01:20:04,320
Well, have a think about it, Margaret.

1061
01:20:04,320 --> 01:20:10,760
Look, Len, what you all suffered
at Bindoon, that's your history.

1062
01:20:10,760 --> 01:20:12,273
But it's not mine.

1063
01:20:14,480 --> 01:20:17,160
I have to be careful.

1064
01:20:17,160 --> 01:20:18,320
I...

1065
01:20:18,320 --> 01:20:23,400
I'm not, um... It wouldn't be appropriate for me
to get too close to all of that.

1066
01:20:23,400 --> 01:20:27,640
It's... Well, it wouldn't be right.

1067
01:20:27,640 --> 01:20:30,040
No, no, you'll be right.
I'll look after you.

1068
01:20:30,040 --> 01:20:32,315
No, Len, I don't want to.

1069
01:20:33,600 --> 01:20:37,434
I don't have to go there and I don't want to.

1070
01:20:38,560 --> 01:20:41,840
OK, OK, but look at it
from the old boys' point of view.

1071
01:20:41,840 --> 01:20:45,040
That's like saying that
you can't look at who they are.

1072
01:20:45,040 --> 01:20:48,120
Is that what they're saying?

1073
01:20:48,120 --> 01:20:50,960
Well, you have a think about it, Margaret.

1074
01:20:50,960 --> 01:20:53,720
Maybe that's the monster living in your head.

1075
01:20:53,720 --> 01:20:57,440
I don't like to think of you walking around

1076
01:20:57,440 --> 01:20:59,431
with a monster like that in your head.

1077
01:21:23,080 --> 01:21:25,360
Well, we should be there in a couple of hours.

1078
01:21:25,360 --> 01:21:28,400
It used to take six before they graded the road.

1079
01:21:28,400 --> 01:21:31,120
God You should have seen it -

1080
01:21:31,120 --> 01:21:34,640
40 or 50 little nippers bouncing around
in the back of an open truck,

1081
01:21:34,640 --> 01:21:37,480
eating dust and flies, crying for their mums.

1082
01:21:37,480 --> 01:21:40,472
We thought we'd been dropped off
at the end of the earth.

1083
01:22:23,800 --> 01:22:25,119
You right?

1084
01:22:45,080 --> 01:22:47,150
See it from here first.

1085
01:23:13,480 --> 01:23:15,280
Is it what you expected?

1086
01:23:15,280 --> 01:23:17,874
I didn't know it would be so big.

1087
01:23:19,280 --> 01:23:22,040
And I didn't know it would be so beautiful.

1088
01:23:22,040 --> 01:23:25,760
The boys put every stone
of that building together.

1089
01:23:25,760 --> 01:23:27,751
I know.

1090
01:23:30,880 --> 01:23:34,080
The cement would burn your feet.

1091
01:23:34,080 --> 01:23:35,720
We'd no shoes.

1092
01:23:35,720 --> 01:23:38,960
The cement would burn the cuts on our feet

1093
01:23:38,960 --> 01:23:41,520
and the sores on our hands and knees.

1094
01:23:41,520 --> 01:23:47,640
All day, in blazing heat, no rest, no water.

1095
01:23:47,640 --> 01:23:54,239
I was nine years old and I was lifting rocks
the size of my upper body.

1096
01:23:55,920 --> 01:24:02,760
And he's yelling at us,
'You weak, weak, pitiful sons of whores.'

1097
01:24:02,760 --> 01:24:05,880
We built stations of the cross.

1098
01:24:05,880 --> 01:24:09,000
But who was crucified, huh?

1099
01:24:09,000 --> 01:24:10,911
Tell me that.

1100
01:24:12,440 --> 01:24:13,960
You all right to go down?

1101
01:24:13,960 --> 01:24:16,840
Suppose they don't let us in.

1102
01:24:16,840 --> 01:24:19,720
There's a swimming pool
at the back of the building.

1103
01:24:19,720 --> 01:24:22,632
I paid for it. They'll let us in.

1104
01:24:55,120 --> 01:24:58,600
He had this... he had this big knobby stick.

1105
01:24:58,600 --> 01:25:03,480
And he would crack you over the skull with it.

1106
01:25:03,480 --> 01:25:07,120
Leather belts. Fanbelt from the tractor.

1107
01:25:07,120 --> 01:25:10,157
Anything that would give you
a good wallop, you know?

1108
01:25:13,200 --> 01:25:16,112
They'll still be having their breakfast.
Feel like a cup of tea?

1109
01:25:17,880 --> 01:25:19,199
Come on.

1110
01:25:59,120 --> 01:26:00,678
Morning, brothers.

1111
01:26:05,360 --> 01:26:07,400
I've brought Mrs. Humphreys

1112
01:26:07,400 --> 01:26:09,868
to have a look around the old place
if that's all right.

1113
01:26:13,480 --> 01:26:14,959
Come through.

1114
01:26:31,120 --> 01:26:32,599
There we go.

1115
01:26:37,000 --> 01:26:38,592
Is there any chance of a cuppa?

1116
01:27:17,480 --> 01:27:20,711
We can do better than a chipped cup,
can't we, brother?

1117
01:27:26,840 --> 01:27:30,280
<i>We'd hear one of the brothers coming.</i>

1118
01:27:30,280 --> 01:27:33,080
Just his footsteps on the wooden floor.

1119
01:27:33,080 --> 01:27:37,080
You'd be lying there in the wet sheets
and you're thinking,

1120
01:27:37,080 --> 01:27:41,880
'Oh, please, God...
Please, God, don't let it be me.'

1121
01:27:41,880 --> 01:27:44,360
He would make you strip naked

1122
01:27:44,360 --> 01:27:49,960
and get on the tables
with everybody watching you.

1123
01:27:49,960 --> 01:27:53,760
Don't know where I thought I could run to,
there's nothing there for miles.

1124
01:27:53,760 --> 01:27:57,320
He came after me on horseback.

1125
01:27:57,320 --> 01:27:59,595
When he caught me...

1126
01:28:01,360 --> 01:28:03,880
..he tied me to a tree.

1127
01:28:03,880 --> 01:28:05,880
And he, uh...

1128
01:28:05,880 --> 01:28:08,678
He...

1129
01:28:13,480 --> 01:28:16,233
<i>You probably can't believe me.</i>

1130
01:28:23,640 --> 01:28:25,995
<i>Of course I believe you.</i>

1131
01:28:32,360 --> 01:28:35,557
The fucker raped me, Margaret.

1132
01:28:38,720 --> 01:28:41,640
Hey, I think you might have
forgotten something, brother.

1133
01:28:44,760 --> 01:28:46,671
I'll fix it up, shall I?

1134
01:29:00,640 --> 01:29:04,800
Didn't matter if he split your skull open,
he'd keep whacking away.

1135
01:29:04,800 --> 01:29:07,600
You just thought...

1136
01:29:07,600 --> 01:29:10,520
'I'm nothing now.

1137
01:29:10,520 --> 01:29:12,988
Nothing at all.'

1138
01:29:15,080 --> 01:29:17,913
Who's gonna... Who's gonna look after me?

1139
01:29:19,720 --> 01:29:23,269
Who's gonna look after me? I'm nobody.

1140
01:29:45,320 --> 01:29:48,360
Have I disturbed you, brothers?

1141
01:29:48,360 --> 01:29:51,272
Have I frightened you?

1142
01:29:53,640 --> 01:29:56,360
What have you got to be frightened of?

1143
01:29:56,360 --> 01:29:58,828
Grown men like you.

1144
01:30:35,000 --> 01:30:37,440
Look at that, Margaret.

1145
01:30:37,440 --> 01:30:41,228
Can't see another house. Nothing but bush.

1146
01:30:42,680 --> 01:30:45,069
No-one would find you here.

1147
01:30:48,240 --> 01:30:51,840
He'd wait for me after dark, Brother Norman.

1148
01:30:51,840 --> 01:30:55,080
He took a shine to me.
I was a favourite, I suppose.

1149
01:30:55,080 --> 01:30:57,674
I don't know.

1150
01:30:58,120 --> 01:31:02,557
You just think, 'I'll live through this.
It'll stop one day.'

1151
01:31:05,640 --> 01:31:07,437
Bloody years.

1152
01:31:12,680 --> 01:31:16,040
Margaret, have a look at that.
Black cockatoo.

1153
01:31:16,040 --> 01:31:19,080
Oh, there'd be flocks of them
over here sometimes.

1154
01:31:19,080 --> 01:31:21,400
They'd sound like trains going over your head.

1155
01:31:21,400 --> 01:31:24,480
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1156
01:31:24,480 --> 01:31:26,040
You've gone a funny colour.

1157
01:31:26,040 --> 01:31:27,758
I'll just get you a drink.

1158
01:31:41,280 --> 01:31:42,793
There you go.

1159
01:31:45,080 --> 01:31:47,400
- You right?
- I'm fine. It's just the heat.

1160
01:31:47,400 --> 01:31:48,520
OK.

1161
01:31:48,520 --> 01:31:51,840
Know what your problem is, Mrs. H?
You don't look after yourself properly.

1162
01:31:51,840 --> 01:31:53,560
You won't let anyone else do it either.

1163
01:31:53,560 --> 01:31:55,760
Len, it's not for anybody else to look after me.

1164
01:31:55,760 --> 01:31:58,320
I've been loved and looked after my entire life.

1165
01:31:58,320 --> 01:31:59,360
It's your turn now.

1166
01:31:59,360 --> 01:32:01,200
But you'll never get it.

1167
01:32:01,200 --> 01:32:05,080
Everybody thinks there's going to be
this big cathartic moment

1168
01:32:05,080 --> 01:32:07,480
when the wrongs are righted
and the wounds healed,

1169
01:32:07,480 --> 01:32:09,040
but it's not going to happen.

1170
01:32:09,040 --> 01:32:12,555
I can't give you back what you've lost.

1171
01:32:15,280 --> 01:32:17,920
Well, there's plenty of other people
in that boat.

1172
01:32:17,920 --> 01:32:21,037
Well, its not enough, is it, Len?
It's never enough.

1173
01:32:24,560 --> 01:32:27,640
Jeez, old Bindoon,
it shook you up all right, didn't it?

1174
01:32:27,640 --> 01:32:29,073
No, I'm fine.

1175
01:32:31,040 --> 01:32:34,160
It should shake me up.
I'm the one who should be shaking.

1176
01:32:34,160 --> 01:32:40,240
But even if I was lying here in the dirt
bawling like a kid,

1177
01:32:40,240 --> 01:32:42,920
I couldn't feel it all, could I?

1178
01:32:42,920 --> 01:32:44,717
Isn't that what you'd tell me?

1179
01:32:45,920 --> 01:32:49,560
I had to stop crying when I was eight.
I don't know how to start now.

1180
01:32:49,560 --> 01:32:52,600
But you feel it.

1181
01:32:52,600 --> 01:32:56,160
You feel it for all of us
because we can't, you do.

1182
01:32:56,160 --> 01:32:59,400
No, you're fighting for us, Margaret.
You're in there for us.

1183
01:32:59,400 --> 01:33:00,920
You're on our side.

1184
01:33:00,920 --> 01:33:03,280
So let the rest go.

1185
01:33:03,280 --> 01:33:07,239
Just let the rest go.

1186
01:33:09,280 --> 01:33:11,350
What you're doing is enough.

1187
01:33:14,120 --> 01:33:16,680
It's more than anyone
else has ever given me.

1188
01:33:48,760 --> 01:33:50,591
Happy Christmas.

1189
01:33:52,560 --> 01:33:55,199
- And happy Christmas.
- Oh!

1190
01:33:58,640 --> 01:34:00,119
Ooh!

1191
01:34:04,520 --> 01:34:07,034
Happy Christmas, darling.

1192
01:34:14,080 --> 01:34:15,832
Here you go, love.

1193
01:34:16,360 --> 01:34:17,840
Happy Christmas.

1194
01:34:17,840 --> 01:34:20,760
So, what are you going to give all of us
for Christmas, Ben?

1195
01:34:20,760 --> 01:34:23,513
I gave you my mum.

1196
01:34:30,080 --> 01:34:31,680
So you did.

1197
01:34:31,680 --> 01:34:35,240
So you did, darling, and we love you for it.

1198
01:34:35,240 --> 01:34:36,798
Hear, hear.

1199
01:34:58,880 --> 01:35:01,040
Hey, don't do that. Don't do that.

1200
01:35:01,040 --> 01:35:03,759
Don't start snivelling.

1201
01:35:05,400 --> 01:35:08,073
Bloody hell, woman,
what are you trying to do to me?

1202
01:35:14,520 --> 01:35:17,398
- See you in a couple of weeks.
- See you in a couple of weeks.

1203
01:38:16,760 --> 01:38:19,880
♪ CAT STEVENS:
Now That I've Lost Everything to You

1204
01:38:19,880 --> 01:38:23,080
♪ You say you want to start something new

1205
01:38:23,080 --> 01:38:26,440
♪ And it's breaking my heart you're leavin'

1206
01:38:26,440 --> 01:38:28,520
♪ Baby, I'm grievin'

1207
01:38:28,520 --> 01:38:31,640
♪ If you want to leave, take good care

1208
01:38:31,640 --> 01:38:34,840
♪ Hope you find a lot of nice things to wear

1209
01:38:34,840 --> 01:38:39,311
♪ Then a lot of nice things turn bad out there

1210
01:38:42,120 --> 01:38:45,908
♪ Oh, baby, baby, it's a wild world

1211
01:38:47,880 --> 01:38:51,714
♪ It's hard to get by just upon a smile

1212
01:38:53,880 --> 01:38:57,873
♪ Oh, baby, baby, it's a wild world

1213
01:38:59,480 --> 01:39:04,679
♪ And I'll always remember you
like a child, girl. ♪

